12. ALFONSO — THE PATRON AXIS + DRIFT (the tug-of-war made mechanical)  [PROPOSED — iterating]
=====================================================================
Builds on `The Sentient Sword` Sec. IX (DRIFT) + Sec. IV (the two patrons). Goal: stop
playing the patron tug-of-war as on/off vibes; make it a deep, SYMMETRIC system where
BOTH gods have a win, there is a SYNTHESIS, and the longer he stays iron the more Peryite
recedes and Namira fills the vacuum. NOT canon yet — develop here, apply on sign-off.

CORE: TWO COUPLED METERS (split what was conflated)
- METER 1 — DRIFT (the forgetting clock): 0% -> 100% of his OWN self-image template gone.
  The DOOM TIMER. Rises with time spent IRON (Dormant or Wakeful — the free-rust-healing
  loophole IS the slide toward forgetting). Falls with time spent REFORMED/embodied
  (re-inhabiting relearns the body). Maxing it = THE CLIFF.
- METER 2 — THE PATRON AXIS (the steering): PERYITE <- P3·P2·P1·[BALANCE]·N1·N2·N3 -> NAMIRA.
  Does not doom him; decides WHERE the doom lands. (More stages than the old binary — the
  symmetry the GM asked for.)

HOW THE METERS MOVE
- Drift UP: time as iron.  Drift DOWN: time reformed.
- Axis toward PERYITE: reforming, doing the work, spreading plague on schedule, USING
  Peryite gifts. (Peryite wants him EMBODIED -> leaning Peryite keeps Drift LOW.)
- Axis toward NAMIRA: staying formless, feeding/consuming, using the allure, USING Namira
  gifts. (Namira wants him FORMLESS -> leaning Namira drives Drift UP.)
- THE RATCHET (= the reversibility answer): TIME is reversible, but POWER USED is NOT.
  Each time he uses a god's gift it leaves a PERMANENT notch toward that god, even if he
  later reforms. This is what makes BALANCE (synthesis) hard — every gift drags you off-center.
- NATURAL PAIRING: Namira = the lazy coast toward the cliff (free healing, dwindle). Peryite
  = may never reach the cliff (lives embodied). Synthesis = must thread the middle on purpose.

THE AXIS = FORM/CYCLE/MORTALITY (Peryite) vs FORMLESSNESS/VOID/IMMORTALITY (Namira)
  [CORRECTED & LORE-GROUNDED — GM 2026-06-30; full lore now saved to the theology book,
   `Lore Books/Gods and Demons` — the Peryite + Namira entries (the opposed halves of decay).]
- The two Princes are COSMOLOGICAL OPPOSITES, and that opposition IS the axis:
    PERYITE = form, the CYCLE, decay-as-RENEWAL (the dead log hosts more life), holding the
      world OUT of the formless ooze. Near-AEDRIC (does the thankless work, no glory, sustains
      Creation — Y'ffre's successor in function). To serve him = accept MORTALITY, because the
      cycle requires that things die so things may grow.
    NAMIRA = formlessness, the VOID, the primordial ooze, decay-as-DISSOLUTION (eat to become
      nothing; "you end the cycle"). Immortality-as-dwindling that terminates in being nothing.
- EMPOWERMENT vs POWER [GM correction — key]: Peryite does not hand out dominion. He gives
  EMPOWERMENT — being made genuinely ABLE to fulfill your role (Alfonso's Living Rot that
  out-competes Antoine's sterile strain; the sustainable-vector synthesis; the capacity to BE
  the thing). NAMIRA is the one who deals POWER — the Crown, Devouring Command, King's Feast,
  dominion, frenzy. So "Peryite offers no candy" was WRONG: he has already given Alfonso
  enormous empowerment. It just isn't flashy dominion, and it comes with the demand to die.
- "SPREADING DEATH REQUIRES DYING" [GM correction — collapses two fates into one]: per Peryite,
  you cannot embody a process you exempt yourself from. So becoming ROT-INCARNATE / the-thing-
  that-spreads-dying is NOT separate from dying yourself — it REQUIRES it. Rot-incarnate is the
  PERYITE ending (below), not the synthesis. The lich is the exact heresy: the one rotting thing
  that refuses to rot away.
- THE INVERSION (the trap's teeth): the LAZY/default path is NAMIRA — do nothing, rest as iron
  for free rust heals, coast past the cliff into locked deathless void. The PERYITE path has a
  DEADLINE and takes active COURAGE: choosing death, an end, vulnerability, while you still can.

THE CLIFF — recast: DRIFT maxing = he has forgotten too much of his FLESH to EVER RETURN TO IT.
  The cliff is the LAST MOMENT he could still choose mortality. After it, the door to flesh is
  shut and only the deathless paths remain. Peryite's win must be taken BEFORE the cliff, racing
  the Drift; Namira's win is what you get by letting the clock run out.

THE THREE FATES (meant to weigh EQUALLY; only synthesis is a clean "good" ending):
  > NAMIRA / THE VOID (the default/lazy doom — and the WORST ending): let Drift max. Locked
      IMMORTAL and FORMLESS forever — can never be flesh again, and doesn't want to be. The
      lodestone, consuming emptiness, decay that spreads by UN-MAKING form. No form, no self, NO
      DEATH. This is the worst of the three by far: even MEHRUNES DAGON wants existence to
      continue (to be torn down and remade); Namira's telos is the return to NOTHING. (What
      happens to a player who just rests for free rust heals and never steers.) [Crown-fuse
      flavor as before; the hard rule "never WORN" still stands — catastrophe to author, not a
      scripted beat.]
      HER SEDUCTION = THE DEVOURING MOTHER (this is her gift-ladder / why the lazy path tempts):
      Namira is patron of the outcast, the disregarded, the one who has lost his form — and she
      PROTECTS and EMPOWERS them (belonging, the allure, feeding, "rebirth," the Spirit-Queen
      duality of giving-and-taking). BUT only so long as they stay broken and hers. The moment a
      follower betters himself / reaches for the light (= takes the Peryite path), she withdraws
      everything. Her love needs him small. So her gifts read as care and homecoming and feel
      good to take — and every one ties him tighter to the dark and harder to leave (THE RATCHET,
      thematically grounded). Play her as the mother who keeps you sick because she needs to be
      needed. [THEMATIC RHYME — use it: Namira is to Alfonso what ISMARA is to Davinia — the
